To adapt the `StreamService::searchContent` method to work with the provided files and their details, you should update it to search through the `content_` vector, comparing the provided `partial` string with each content's name. If `partial` equals "*", the method should return IDs of all content. Otherwise, it should only include content whose names contain the `partial` substring. Here’s how you could implement this with the given class structure:

```cpp
std::vector<CID_T> StreamService::searchContent(const std::string& partial) const {
    std::vector<CID_T> results;

    // Iterate over all content items
    for(size_t i = 0; i < content_.size(); i++) {
        // Assuming Content class has a method 'name()' that returns the content's name as a std::string
        const std::string& contentName = content_[i]->name();  // Use -> because content_ is a vector of pointers

        // Check for the "*" case to return all content IDs
        if (partial == "*") {
            results.push_back(content_[i]->id());  // Add the content's ID to the results
        } 
        // Otherwise, only add the content ID if the partial string is found in the content's name
        else if (contentName.find(partial) != std::string::npos) {
            results.push_back(content_[i]->id());  // Similarly, add the content's ID to the results
        }
    }

    return results;
}
```

